sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159112
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: FRET Reporter for TEV Protease activity (eCFP_TEV-site-linker_SYFP2) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes a FRET reporter with the chromophores eCFP and SYFP2 that is seperated by a TEV cleavage site. As a FRET pair, excitation of eCFP leads to a energy transfer from eCFP to SYFP2 (FRET) resulting in a fluorescence of SYFP2. In the presence of TEV Protease cleavage actitivy the FRET pair SYFP2 is cleaved off from eCFP and eCFP is not anymore quenched by SYFP2 resulting in the fluorescence of eCFP. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159302
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Enhanced Cyan Fluorescent Protein (eCFP) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This Biobricks is a improved version BBa_E0020 which codes for the Enhanced Cyan Fluorescent Protein. We improve the function of the biobrick, to allow protein fusions which is originally not possible due to RFC[10] pre- and suffix. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG
